   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Launch Microsoft Word. Open a new document or the document you want to work with.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the X-Author add-in as described in <xref href="../installing_x_author_contr_45220121/45220121.xml" format="dita">Installing X-Author Contracts</xref>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>After the X-Author add-in pane loads, hover over the  icon on the left-hand side to display the login menu.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image height="400"
                         placement="break"
                         href="../attachments/45711457/49676296.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Depending on the org you want to connect to, select <uicontrol>Sign-In to Production</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Sign-In to Sandbox</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>If it is the first time you are logging into the org, you will be prompted to allow X-Author to access Salesforce. Click <uicontrol>Allow</uicontrol> to proceed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter your Salesforce credentials to log in.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <result id="result_bqk_lcq_12c">
